Text areas come in four different default sizes (heights). This is the size they will appear initially on screen, they can be enlarged by the user if required.

```tsx
() => {
  const SIZES = ['small', 'medium', 'large', 'xlarge'] as const;
  return (
    <div className="flex flex-col gap-4">
      {SIZES.map(size => (
        <div key={size}>
          <ComponentTitle>{size}</ComponentTitle>
          <Textarea size={size} />
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  );
};
```
